{"tid":1241890,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"南韓媒體報導，習帝送咗10萬噸糧食俾金仔","createTime":"2019-06-19T01:02:27.000Z","updateTime":"2019-06-19T07:03:13.000Z","uid":48083,"like":18,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":16,"replies":[{"pid":"5ccf1ee616bd8eef8c0f80fbd0a29353387b5189","tid":1241890,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-19T01:02:27.000Z","msg":"China's Xi Jinping Will Reportedly Give Kim Jong Un 100,000 Tons of Food to Feed Hungry North Koreans<br />\n<br />\nBy Tom O'Connor  On 6/18/19 at 3:02 PM EDT<br />\nChinese President Xi Jinping may be offering up to 100,000 tons of food in humanitarian aid to North Korean supreme leader Kim Jong Un ahead of a historic visit later this week.<br />\n<br />\nBoth Chinese and North Korea state-run media announced Xi's state visit&mdash;the first of its kind since their predecessors met in Pyongyang in 2005&mdash;on Monday. As speculation mounted about what may come out of the fourth meeting between the two men, <strong><span style=\"color: red;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">South Korea's Yonhap News Agency wrote Tuesday that news reports have suggested the 100,000 tons figure as a gesture to shore up relations.</span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\nThe move would also come as North Korea faced a drought brought on by what ruling Korean Workers' Party Central Committee official newspaper Rodong Sinmun described last month as the country's lowest rainfall in a century. On Friday, the official Korean Central News Agency reported that &quot;Drought has been persisting in some areas&quot; of the country.<br />\n⋯⋯⋯<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.newsweek.com/china-north-korea-food-kim-jong-un-1444610\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fchina-north-korea-food-kim-jong-un-1444610&d=HhKtR2wUfRZLc9nBt5dK8FgnvSLZGSqUYyTYHJNLWIM%3D&h=a5bd7c02\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.newsweek.com/china-north-korea-food-kim-jong-un-1444610</a>"},{"pid":"12fa97a72d3e44a6d4c